their was a small coffee, shop on the corner of the street. the smell of fresh brewd coffee filled the air enticing passersby, to stop in for a cup inside cozy chairs and tables were arrange neatly inviting customer to relax and enjoy their drinks, a friendly young woman greeted each customer with a warm smile she took, their orders with effishency and care ensuring that each cup was made to perfection as customers siped on their drinks lively converstaion flowed throughout the shop suddenly the doorbell rang announcing the arrival of a new patron the barista looked up ready to welcome them to the shop
